# Vercel Speed Insights Integration

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js Finance Dashboard application.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 1.3.1
- Updated package.json with the new dependency
- Updated package-lock.json with resolved dependencies

### 2. Root Layout Integration (src/app/layout.js)
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the main layout div
- Placed within the ClientProviders wrapper for proper client-side functionality

## Implementation Details

Since this project uses Next.js 16.1.6 with App Router, I used the recommended approach:
- Imported from `@vercel/speed-insights/next` (automatic route tracking)
- Added the component to the root layout (src/app/layout.js)
- No additional configuration needed - the component automatically tracks page navigation

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ No lint errors introduced in the layout file
✅ All pages continue to render correctly (11 routes verified during build)
✅ Package-lock.json updated with exact dependency versions

## Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package and its dependencies  
- `src/app/layout.js` - Added SpeedInsights import and component

## Notes
- The SpeedInsights component is placed inside the ClientProviders wrapper to ensure it has access to client-side context
- The component will automatically track page views and performance metrics when deployed to Vercel
- No additional configuration is required; Speed Insights will work out of the box on Vercel deployments
